[<p class="sh2"><span>SIGN UP</span> FOR OUR NEWSLETTER</p>, <p>The report\xa0explains that non-citizens\xa0who illegally voted in 2008, and who electorally \u201ctended\xa0to favor Democrats\u201d, could have handed\xa0the 2008 Minnesota Senate\xa0election\xa0to\xa0Al Franken, which gave Senate Democrats the \u201cpivotal 60th vote needed to overcome filibusters in order to pass health-care reform and other Obama administration priorities in the 111th Congress,\u201d the report writes.</p>, <p class="sh2"><span>SIGN UP</span> FOR OUR NEWSLETTER</p>, <p>The 2014\xa0<em>Washington Post</em>\xa0article titled \u201cCould Non-Citizens Decide The November Election?\u201d was written by Jesse Richman and David Earnest, two associate professors of Political Science and International Studies at Old Dominion University.\xa0Their research relied upon\xa0data\xa0from the Cooperative Congressional Election Study (CCES).</p>, <p>The professors <a href="/web/20161020174827/http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0261379414000973">found</a> \u201cthat\xa0some non-citizens participate in U.S. elections, and that this participation has been large enough to change meaningful election outcomes including Electoral College votes, and Congressional elections.\u201d</p>, <p>As the\xa0<em>Washington Post</em> article\xa0stated:</p>, <p>The report came the same week that the North Carolina State Board of Elections\xa0<a href="/web/20161020174827/http://www.breitbart.com/Big-Government/2014/10/22/Ineligible-DACA-Beneficiaries-Discovered-On-NC-Voting-Rolls">found</a>\xa0the names of 145\xa0individuals on voting rolls who were\xa0ineligible to vote because they were illegal\xa0immigrants who had been recipients of Obama\u2019s 2012 executive amnesty (DACA).</p>, <p>As\xa0<em>Breitbart\u2019s\xa0</em>Caroline May reported at the time:</p>, <p>According to a\xa0<em>Winston-Salem Journal</em>\xa0<a href="/web/20161020174827/http://www.journalnow.com/news/elections/state/dmv-search-of-records-turns-up-ineligible-n-c-voters/article_f4ecc2ae-5981-11e4-9f35-0017a43b2370.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank">report</a>, the State Board of Elections discovered the potential illegal voters\u2026 when the N.C. Division of Motor Vehicles ran a search for DACA licenses\u2026\xa0DACA beneficiaries in North Carolina are able to obtain drivers licenses, but they are not able to vote.\xa0The<em>\xa0Journal</em>\xa0<a href="/web/20161020174827/http://www.journalnow.com/news/elections/state/dmv-search-of-records-turns-up-ineligible-n-c-voters/article_f4ecc2ae-5981-11e4-9f35-0017a43b2370.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank">notes</a>\xa0that it is likely more ineligible people may still remain on the voting rolls. \u201cNearly 10,000 names on the rolls are tagged by the DMV as \u2018legally present,\u2019 according to elections and transportation officials. But that doesn\u2019t mean that all 10,000 are ineligible to vote at this time. These are license holders who were not U.S. citizens when they got a license.\u201d [\u2026]\xa0According to the report, earlier this month the SBOE officials did a sample cross-check of 1,600 of the 10,000 \u201clegally present\u201d names against a Department of Homeland Security database and found\u2026 that six percent were ineligible [to vote], meaning if the ratio held for the whole 10,000, 600 people would be ineligible.</p>, <p>During a recent North Carolina rally,\xa0Donald Trump\xa0warned that\xa0the election is\xa0being \u201crigged\u201d.\xa0Trump later tweeted:</p>, <p dir="ltr" lang="en">The election is absolutely being rigged by the dishonest and distorted media pushing Crooked Hillary \u2013 but also at many polling places \u2013 SAD</p>, <p>\u2014 Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) <a href="/web/20161020174827/https://twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/787699930718695425">October 16, 2016</a></p>, <p><script async="" charset="utf-8" src="/web/20161020174827js_/http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"></script></p>, <p>Despite its own reporting on voter fraud and the role non-citizen foreign nationals likely\xa0had in delivering\xa0Democratic victories in close elections, the <em>Washington Post</em>\xa0now seems to be disregarding\xa0its own coverage on the issue in order to characterize Trump\u2019s claims as\xa0\u201c<a href="/web/20161020174827/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/10/17/donald-trumps-ridiculous-claims-about-voter-fraud-are-an-embarrassment/">ridiculous</a>,\u201d \u201c<a href="/web/20161020174827/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/trump-claims-election-is-rigged-and-calls-for-pre-debate-drug-tests/2016/10/15/25d4d682-930e-11e6-9c52-0b10449e33c4_story.html?tid=a_inl">unsubstantiated</a>\u201d and <a href="/web/20161020174827/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/inside-donald-trumps-echo-chamber-of-conspiracies-grievances-and-vitriol/2016/10/16/1c3c6a72-921e-11e6-9c85-ac42097b8cc0_story.html?postshare=2361476656172801&amp;tid=ss_tw">part</a> of <a href="/web/20161020174827/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/10/17/donald-trumps-ridiculous-claims-about-voter-fraud-are-an-embarrassment/">\u201cbroad conspiracy theories\u201d.</a></p>, <p>House Speaker\xa0Paul Ryan has similarly\xa0sought\xa0to denounce the concerns of voter fraud expressed by\xa0his\xa0Party\u2019s nominee\u2013 insisting that\xa0the election results will be\xa0inherently secure.\xa0Ryan\u2019s spokesman told Buzzfeed\xa0that the Republican House Speaker\xa0is \u201cfully confident\u201d the election will be carried out \u201cwith integrity\u201d.</p>, <p>The statement from Ryan\u2019s office is remarkable given the fact that, as the 2014\xa0<em>Washington Post</em>\xa0report suggests, the health care law Ryan\xa0claims to oppose may\xa0only have been possible because non-citizen foreign nationals illegally cast their ballots in U.S.\xa0elections.</p>]